 Tonya Harding's emotional plea to remain on the Olympic team because she wants 
to represent her country is complete bunk. Money and fame are her prime 
motivators. As a two-time Olympian and a Vietnam veteran, I say that 100% of 
the athletes who ever qualified for the U.S. Olympic team did it for 
themselves.  
</P>
<P>
 If she wants to represent her country, she should politely withdraw her 
position on the Olympic figure skating team before she is further embarrassed 
and seek out her local Army recruiter. 
</P>
