<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; LECONTE FOLLOWS BIG VICTORY WITH QUICK LOSS TO BOETSCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arnaud Boetsch beat fellow Frenchman Henri Leconte, 6-2, 6-4, Friday in the 
Marseille Open, a day after Leconte ousted Boris Becker. 
</P>
<P>
 Boetsch, seeded fifth, took advantage of several faults by Leconte to win in 1 
hour 15 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Top-seeded Michael Stich of Germany beat Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden, 7-5, 7-6 
(9-7); defending champion Marc Rosset of Switzerland defeated Czech David Rikl, 
7-6 (7-4), 7-5, and Diego Nargiso of Italy, a qualifier who made the main draw, 
defeated Tomas Carbonell of Spain, 6-1, 7-6 (9-7). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Martina Navratilova defeated Larisa Neiland of Latvia, 6-4, 6-4, in the 
quarterfinals of the Toray Pan Pacific Open at Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
 Steffi Graf needed only 42 minutes to beat Jana Nejedly, 6-1, 6-1; Manuela 
Maleeva-Fragniere defeated Marketa Kochta of Germany, 6-4, 6-4, and Kristie 
Boogert of the Netherlands beat Pam Shriver, 6-1, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Alexander Volkov survived a scare from Sweden's Henrik Holm before the 
eighth-seeded Russian advanced to the semifinals of the Dubai Open at United 
Arab Emirates. 
</P>
<P>
 Volkov, ranked 20th in the world, won six of the last seven games for a 6-4, 
0-6, 7-5 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Fifth-seeded Ivan Lendl was forced to retire during the third set of his match 
because of a back injury. Fourth-seeded Magnus Gustafsson won, 4-6, 6-2, 3-1. 
</P>
