<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEPPERDINE BACK ON TRACK, 77-64 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MITCH POLIN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After losing to Loyola Marymount last week, Pepperdine was on the verge of 
falling out of the West Coast Conference title race. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Waves climbed back into contention with a 77-64 victory over Portland 
Friday night before 2,413 at Firestone Fieldhouse in Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 Forward Dana Jones, the Waves' leading scorer the last two seasons, had a 
career-high 31 points and added 14 rebounds as Pepperdine, 12-7 overall and 4-3 
in the WCC, moved into a four-way tie for second with Portland, San Francisco 
and Santa Clara.  
</P>
<P>
 The Waves also pulled to within two games of Gonzaga. Pepperdine plays its 
next two games against the Bulldogs, including tonight at Malibu. 
</P>
<P>
 "Now we can control our own destiny," Coach Tom Asbury said. 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine shot 51.6% in the first half against Portland (11-11, 4-3) and led 
by as many as 14 points before settling for a 38-28 halftime lead. 
</P>
