<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO MORE 'SHADOWS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In reference to your article ("Putting the Shadow in His Place," Jan. 6), 
reader Zita Carno was correct in stating that Orson Welles was "The Shadow" in 
1937-38 ("Welles' 'Shadow,' " Saturday Letters, Jan. 15).However, it is very 
important to acknowledge the two "Shadows" who followed Welles. Bill Johnstone 
played the lead from the 1939 to the 1945 season. 
</P>
<P>
 Bret Morrison, probably the actor most of us remember as "The Shadow," 
followed Johnstone until the series ended in 1954. 
</P>
<P>
 MARTY HALPERIN, Archivist 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Pioneer Broadcasters 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood 
</P>
