<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH COAST LEAGUE ROUNDUP; SAN CLEMENTE EXTENDS SLIDE FOR COUGARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Graham Gary made three of four free throws in overtime, and Luke Mannix added 
a three-point basket and two free throws as San Clemente upset Capistrano 
Valley, 78-76, in a South Coast League boys' basketball game Friday night at 
San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fourth loss in five games for Capistrano Valley (15-8, 4-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Mannix and Phinney Gardner scored 21 points each for San Clemente (11-11, 
2-6). Brandon Puffer scored 16 points, 12 in the fourth quarter and overtime, 
for Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 In other South Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 105, El Toro 47 -- Top-ranked Mater Dei scored more than 100 points 
for the third time this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Miles Simon led the Monarchs (24-0, 8-0) with 21 points, 12 assists and seven 
steals. Schea Cotton and Clay McKnight (four three-pointers) each added 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Lewis led El Toro (10-13, 2-6) with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 65, Mission Viejo 51 -- Dimitri Kandis scored 16 points to lead 
Dana Hills (12-11, 5-3). Austin Moherman scored 18 points for Mission Viejo 
(9-12, 3-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
