</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 5, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 10; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
161 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY LEAGUE ROUNDUP; TROY RALLIES TO GET PAST BUENA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Troy rallied from an 11-point deficit for a 63-51 victory over Buena Park on 
Friday to remain in sole possession of first place in the Freeway League. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park took an 11-point lead in the third quarter before the Warriors 
(16-8, 7-1) came back.Junior James Hampson, who had 19 points, made four 
three-pointers in the second half and Jeff Sand added 19 points, including two 
three-pointers, to lead Troy. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Smith scored 14 points and Ruben Gasso added 13 for Buena Park (3-20, 
0-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 51, Fullerton 49 -- Sergio Hernandez scored 14 points, Chad Fister had 
13 and Nathan Mirth added 11, including three three-pointers to lead Sonora 
(19-5, 6-2), the ninth-ranked team in the county. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Schatz scored 13 points and Sam Mankiewicz and Matt Sanders each added 12 
for Fullerton (12-12, 3-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 55, La Habra 47 -- Ben Nicolas scored 16 points and Mike SooHoo 
added 15 points for host Sunny Hills (10-14, 4-4). 
</P>
