<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; SANTA ANA VALLEY BEATS FOOTHILL, SETS SCHOOL RECORD 
FOR VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Riggins scored 28 points, 12 on three-pointers, as No. 4-ranked Santa 
Ana Valley set a school record for boys' basketball victories in a season with 
a 75-52 victory over Foothill in a Century League game Friday at Santa Ana 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Darnell Adamson had 19 points and 14 rebounds, and Olujimi Mann added 17 
points and 12 assists for Santa Ana Valley (21-3, 7-1). 
</P>
<P>
 John Brittingham had 16 points and Erick Williams added 12 points for Foothill 
(9-15, 3-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Century League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 67, Villa Park 54 -- Senior forward Pat Harris led third-ranked Orange 
with 16 points and eight rebounds. Jason Krauss had 15 points and seven 
rebounds for the Panthers (20-2, 8-0). Chip Bernards had a game-high 26 points 
with five three-pointers for Villa Park (3-18, 0-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Express League: 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach Claremont 65, Bethel Baptist 40 -- Steve Kimble had 32 
points, 18 rebounds and 10 assists and Derick Simpson added 11 points to lead 
Huntington Beach Claremont (6-9, 3-9). 
