<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; RANCHO ALAMITOS STILL IN HUNT WITH VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos, trying to win its fourth consecutive Garden Grove League 
championship, kept its hopes alive Friday by defeating Kennedy, 63-49. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm going to get my first league championship this year," Rancho Alamitos 
Coach Peter Pyle said."And some of the girls on the team will be winning their 
fourth." 
</P>
<P>
 Those are lofty expectations for the Vaqueros, who need to beat first-place La 
Quinta (12-0 in league) Tuesday at La Quinta and then Santiago on Thursday. If 
they succeed, they still need La Quinta to lose its final game against Kennedy 
for an outright title. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are going to beat (La Quinta)," Pyle said. "We have nothing to lose." 
</P>
<P>
 The Vaqueros started slowly in their victory over Kennedy (15-9, 8-4), leading 
27-26 at halftime. But behind the play of Akilah Rodgers and Sally Vasquez, 
Rancho Alamitos (17-6, 11-1) went on a 14-2 run in the third quarter, giving 
the Vaqueros a 45-31 lead. Rodgers finished the game with 17 points, 19 
rebounds and six blocked shots. Vasquez added 16 points and seven rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Karin Kitagawa led Kennedy with 19 points and Erryn Gutjahr had 11. MELANIE 
NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
