<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS WOMEN END GOLDEN WEST STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress ended Golden West's 25-game Orange Empire Conference women's 
basketball winning streak with a 79-75 victory in overtime Friday at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West, the second-ranked team in the State, last lost in conference to 
Saddleback in February, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Sara Works, a freshman forward, scored 26 points and had 17 rebounds for 
Cypress (20-8, 5-4 in conference), which had lost twice to Golden West this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Works scored Cypress' first six overtime points, all on assists from Jennifer 
Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West rallied to take the lead, 75-74, on a three-pointer by Kristin 
Brun with 2 minutes 30 seconds to play. The Chargers took it back, 76-75, on a 
jumper by Johnson with 1:53 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Stephanie Werdel gave Cypress a 78-75 lead with 1:37 left with a lay-in. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West (26-4, 8-1) rallied from 14 points down with about six minutes to 
play to force overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Deana Itow had a chance to give Golden West the lead with nine seconds left 
but missed a free throw that would have completed a three-point play. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Kravik scored 18 points for Golden West, which leads second-place 
Fullerton by 1 1/2 games. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference women's basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 89, Rancho Santiago 60 -- Bonnie Trejo scored a career-high 27 
points and had 11 rebounds as the Gauchos (7-14, 2-7) stopped a five-game 
losing streak. Rancho Santiago (3-17, 0-9) has lost nine in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 60, Orange Coast 59 (OT) -- Jocelyn Mackzum led Fullerton (18-11, 
6-2) with 18 points and 13 rebounds at Fullerton. LeAnn Kazmer had 18 points 
and 14 rebounds for Orange Coast (17-10, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference basketball men's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 93, Rancho Santiago 79 -- Saddleback made 28 of 29 free throws in 
its eighth consecutive victory. The Gauchos (19-6, 9-1), hold a one-game lead 
over Riverside with four left. 
</P>
<P>
 Josh Borella (15 points) made 10 of 10 free throws, and Tes Whitlock (29) was 
nine for nine. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean Amos scored 22 for Rancho Santiago (18-9, 6-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 78, Fullerton 75 -- Derek Roche had 24 points, including five 
three-pointers, to lead Orange Coast (12-13, 2-8) to the upset, ending a 
seven-game conference losing streak. Tyrone Merriweather had 14 points and 11 
rebounds for Fullerton (21-8, 6-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 85, Golden West 65 -- Jeff Cummins (22 points) made four of five 
three-point shots for visiting Cypress (12-17, 3-7). Golden West is 8-18, 1-9. 
</P>
