<P>
 Chrysler Recalls All New Neons: The auto maker said it is recalling every Neon 
and is closing the plant that builds them for at least a week while it corrects 
a problem that could cause the engine to stall.It also told Dodge and Plymouth 
dealers to quit delivering the new cars until the problem is fixed. The recall, 
announced only a day after Chrysler Corp. marketers outlined their plans to 
capture up to 15% of the subcompact car market in its first year, involves all 
1,300 Neons sold since the car went on the market Jan. 2. This is the second 
recall in recent weeks affecting Chrysler's new lines. 
