<TEXT>
<P>
 Flint Morrison has been installed as president of the California School 
Personnel Commissioners Assn. at the group's annual conference in Burlingame 
recently. 
</P>
<P>
 The state association is made up of more than 90 "merit system" school 
districts throughout the state. 
</P>
<P>
 Morrison, 62, said the merit system determines the promotion of many 
non-teaching school employees through oral and written tests designed to 
determine the merit of the individual. 
</P>
<P>
 The state association conducts training and development sessions for local 
chapters and helps solve difficulties that may arise, Morrison said. 
</P>
<P>
 A former administrator in the Anaheim Union High School District, Morrison has 
been on the Ocean View School District Personnel Commission for 14 years. 
</P>
<P>
 He also is a news anchor and script writer for the Huntington Beach Channel 3 
News over cable television. ROBERT BARKER 
