<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGOURA'S CHARGE TAKES THE STEAM OUT OF SIMI VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Agoura's Brian Ureda made a three-point shot with 11 seconds to play in 
overtime, giving the Chargers a 60-57 victory over Simi Valley in a key 
Marmonte League game Friday night at Thousand Oaks High. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the Pioneers' first loss in four games since Coach Dean Bradshaw was 
suspended. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley (15-6, 6-3 in league play) led by 11 midway through the fourth 
quarter, but two-for-eight free-throw shooting down the stretch helped Agoura 
(15-6, 9-2) come back. 
</P>
<P>
 "The thing I love about this team is that they don't quit," Agoura Coach Kevin 
Pasky said. "All we did was pick up the effort and execute a little better." 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Brian Laibow sparked the Charger comeback by scoring 13 of his 23 
points in the fourth quarter, including a three-pointer to give Agoura a 55-54 
lead with 22 seconds to play in regulation. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley's Jeremy Roberts, who led the Pioneers with 15 points, made one of 
two free throws with 10 seconds to play to send the game into overtime. JEFF 
FLETCHER 
</P>
