RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GIFTS: Wilfred and Mary Jane Von der Ahe of North Hollywood, longtime 
benefactors of Catholic institutions, will donate $3 million in endowment funds 
over the next three years to the Los Angeles archdiocese's three seminaries -- 
Our Lady Queen of Angels High School Seminary in Mission Hills and St. John's 
College and graduate-level seminary in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Interest income from the gifts will endow a faculty chair at each school and 
provide money for scholarships, curriculum enrichment and other projects. 
SERVICE: A service of thanksgiving for surviving the Jan. 17 earthquake will be 
held 5 p.m. Sunday at Holy Shepherd Lutheran Church in Chatsworth. Father 
Robert McNamara, pastor of St. John Eudes Catholic Church in Chatsworth, and 
Rabbi Bernard M. Cohen, director of the Clergy Network, will speak at the 
church at 10347 Mason Ave. 
</P>
