<TEXT>
<P>
 Nation of Islam -- A background box in Friday's editions incorrectly stated 
that the Nation of Islam was based in New York and grew out of the 1960s 
movement led by Malcolm X. The Chicago-based group, which advocates self-help 
and black pride, was founded in the early 1930s by the late Elijah Muhammad. 
</P>
